===Etymology===
Old English ''T&#299wesdæg'', from the Germanic God ''[[w:Tiw|T&#299w]]'' corresponding to the Roman God ''[[w:Mars_(god)|Mars]]'' whence the Latin ''dies marti''
===Noun===
#The third [[day]] of the [[week]]. It follows [[Monday]] and precedes [[Wednesday]].
#The second day of the week in systems using the ISO 8601 norm.
